        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer202106313" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3496174223785408817">I read this book over and over. It&apos;s the one I&apos;d pick to have on a desert island. The way Tozer talks about faith and living the Christian life--he takes what religion has turned into complicated and noncommittal routines and returns to the blessed simplicity of what it means to pursue God, to fully engage your heart with His. I can&apos;t write a review that will do the book justice. It&apos;s a short one and can be read in one day, so see for yourself.</span>
  <span id="freeText3496174223785408817" style="display:none">I read this book over and over. It's the one I'd pick to have on a desert island. The way Tozer talks about faith and living the Christian life--he takes what religion has turned into complicated and noncommittal routines and returns to the blessed simplicity of what it means to pursue God, to fully engage your heart with His. I can't write a review that will do the book justice. It's a short one and can be read in one day, so see for yourself.</span>
